    <title>Re: Time-Based Expansion Progression (Please give input everyone)</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=1123</link>
    <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Abazzagaroth wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;And those arguments are not logically justified.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Higher levels taking over zones/spawns for gear to twink or sell has always happened and will always happen. This idea that a new expansion opens up and casual people all the sudden get the land to themselves is stupid and belied by the fact that mudflation from new expansions just makes it LESS likely casual people get anything that is considered worthwhile, as it becomes perma farmed by much smaller groups of higher level players (especially true through velious with the relative lack of no drop gear).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;When there's a race involved, the hardcore people I'm talking about would just gear up enough to beat the next encounter and keep racing on. You don't see any of the uber guilds nowadays farming group content (unless it's needed somehow for progression).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Not to mention it ignores the historical fact that any time a regular new server has opened up, the &amp;quot;casual&amp;quot; population has ignored old content to push ahead into current content (why grind in lguk when you can go somewhere else for better loot *and* more exp?).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;I never denied this fact - but it doesn't even come into play until Luclin really, the zones in Kunark and Luclin didn't have a huge edge in gear or exp versus original zones of the same level. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If all the &amp;quot;ubers&amp;quot; quit, all that means is it takes longer for expansions to be opened up (sorry, guild raiding is not the same as &amp;quot;uber&amp;quot;), not that they will never open up, and that would be just fine with these people wanting a time limit anyway.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;You're right, I shouldn't have said &amp;quot;never,&amp;quot; but without any hardcore guilds the progression would take so long that I think most players would become frustrated with it. Look at Velious, for example - IIRC, AoW wasn't killed until shortly before the Luclin release. Without any uber raiding guilds, I think this would just take so long that a lot of people would get frustrated and migrate back to their native servers.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I don't see a need for a time limit, unless they allow low level raid targets that will be quickly killed to be the triggers, then i could see maybe a 2 month limit or something short I guess. However, your arguments do not ring true at all.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
