      <description>I'm completely against it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've never been a fan of farming. I'd rather move on once finished with a given area/encounter. If I'm done with all unlocked content but have to wait for weeks or months to continue, I'd probably just cancel. A progression server isn't much of a &amp;quot;progression&amp;quot; server if you can't keep...you know...progressing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Given the time necessary to key up for the end of each expansion, I don't think anything but EQclassic will be finished quickly. It will naturally take months. Those servers that came up 3-4 years into the game during luclin + PoP took nearly a year to catch up WITH access to all existing content. It will inevitably take longer here with the incremental access to content. When I say &amp;quot;nearly a year&amp;quot; I mean that for the most organized, hardcore 10+ hours daily unemployed basement dweller guilds. (I was part of one of them at the time).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I'd bet the fastest most hardcore guild gets to Quarm's corpse in about one year. That's EQclassic + 4 expansions. Ignoring LoY &amp;amp; LDoN, we've still got what, 5 expansions left? That sounds like a nice lineup for year #2 to me.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I don't think condensing 7 years into 2 is unreasonable. I'm certainly not signing up for another 7 years ;p&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Chaan&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
