      <title>Re: Time-Based Expansion Progression (Please give input everyone)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=1091#M1091</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As long as unlocking the expansions requires the most difficult encounters to be beaten (and hopefully a variety of encounters) then there is no need for any sort of time limit.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And don't forget that they can always have other triggers needed too, like, for any expansion that increases the max level they could require X number of characters to be at the max level of the time in addition to certain kills. Or whatever.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you only have to kill the relatively easy encounters, then sure, it probably will open up really fast, but for all we know, this is what the devs *want* to happen. They may envision this server to get 90% caught up in a year or so, and completely caught up in 2 years, and them opening up additional servers like this every 6 months or so, and then slowly contracting older servers if their population falls. Such a strategy, if advertised correctly, might result in more new accounts being started as it gets rid of the major problem non-eq players I know have talked about: they feel like they can never catch up so why bother starting.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
